XGen Protocol — Licensing Notes

This project uses the Business Source License 1.1 (BSL 1.1) during active
development and pre-release phases. The intent is as follows:

1. DEVELOPMENT PHASE (current)
   The source code, documentation, and specification are available for
   reading, study, and non-production use. Commercial use and production
   deployment are not permitted without explicit written permission from
   the Licensor.

2. HANDOVER TRIGGER
   Upon formal handover of the XGen Protocol to the XGen Protocol Foundation
   — a non-profit governance body to be established — all versions of the
   Licensed Work will convert to GPL-2.0-or-later immediately, regardless
   of the four-year fallback date.

3. POST-HANDOVER (GPL phase)
   After the Change Date or handover, the work is fully open source under
   GPL-2.0-or-later. Anyone may use, modify, and distribute the work under
   the terms of the GPL.

4. CONTRIBUTOR LICENSE AGREEMENT (CLA)
   Contributors to the XGen Protocol during the BSL phase must sign a
   Contributor License Agreement (CLA) assigning copyright to the Licensor,
   Jozef Nižnanský, or, upon its establishment, to the XGen Protocol
   Foundation. This ensures the Foundation can execute the BSL → GPL
   transition cleanly.

5. AUTH MODULES AND CERTIFIED EXTENSIONS
   Third-party Auth Modules and certified extensions developed under
   institutional collaboration agreements are subject to separate licensing
   terms defined in those agreements. The protocol specification itself
   remains under BSL / GPL as described above.

The full rationale for this licensing approach is documented in:
  docs/xgen_appendix_b_en.md — How XGen Protocol Funds Itself Without Selling Out

